            <section id="human-control-levels" class="card rounded-2xl p-6 md:p-8">
                <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-amber-400 mb-4">Models of Human Oversight</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-300 mb-6">To manage the risks of autonomous systems, different levels of human control are necessary. These models are essential to prevent users from becoming powerless against opaque algorithmic decisions.</p>
                <div class="space-y-6">
                    <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                        <div class="text-4xl text-amber-400">üë§</div>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-white">Human-in-the-Loop (HITL)</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-300">A human is directly involved in and must approve every individual decision made by the AI.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                        <div class="text-4xl text-amber-400">üëÄ</div>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-white">Human-on-the-Loop (HOTL)</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-300">The AI makes decisions independently, but a human monitors the system and can intervene if necessary.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                        <div class="text-4xl text-amber-400">üëë</div>
                        <div>
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-white">Human-in-Command (HIC)</h4>
                            <p class="text-gray-300">A human oversees the entire system's activity and can override its decisions based on ethical or strategic goals.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

